710751f-b.title: Manhattan: 12th Avenue - 33rd Street
710751f-b.text:
12th Avenue, east side, from W. 33rd (right) to 34th Streets,
showing the cleared area on the south side of W. 34th Street. At
the right is the hay loft on 33rd Street, and on the left, the ex-
tensions to the old Manhattnn Market. The latter are on the north
side of 34th Street and are to be removed according to the New York
Sun of September 16, 1938.
About 1934
Views 1,2,3,4
P. L. Sperr

710752f-a.title: Manhattan: 12th Avenue - 33rd Street
710752f-a.text:
(1)
Twelfth Avenue, north from, but not including, the N.E. corner
of 33rd Street.
June 2, 1931.
L. Sperr.
(2)
Twelfth Avenue, north from Pier 73, North River, at 33rd Street.
January 28, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
Twelfth Avenue, north from, but not including, 33rd Street.
This is nearly the same view as (l), but three years later,
and from a little farther east, so that the observer is look-
ing directly north along the western edge of the avenue itself.
The West Side Elevated Highway is shown as a dark body at the
extreme left.
May 30, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
